1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>- Come on, that's okay.
- It's okay.</i>

2
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:13,867
<i>- Is that right?
- It's right.</i>

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,133
<i>Hey, it's embarrassing.
I am not prepared.</i>

4
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:17,100
<i> Really? You weren't prepared?</i>

5
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:19,833
<i>Bobby, thank you very much
for coming.</i>

6
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,633
<i>- Happy birthday, Mayor.
- Hey, thank you!</i>

7
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:22,933
<i> Mayor, my gift to you.</i>

8
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,700
<i> This is so beautiful.</i>

9
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,100
<i> Isn't it perfect for me?</i>

10
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,033
<i>I'll be back, I just have
to talk to someone, huh?</i>

11
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:29,500
<i>- Okay. Father...
- Okay.</i>

12
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:30,767
<i> Is it true what I heard?</i>

13
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:33,000
<i> Sorry, it took a while.</i>

14
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:36,600
<i>This is the biggest
and best gift</i>

15
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:38,100
<i>I've ever been given in my life.</i>

16
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:41,667
<i>I wish you and Faye
were the only children I had.</i>

17
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,033
<i> Get down!</i>

18
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>- That's gunshots!
- It's coming from there!</i>

19
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> Dizon!</i>

20
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:48,033
<i>Monty, get out of there! Hurry!</i>

21
00:00:48,167 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>Boss, thank you so much
for letting me escape.</i>

22
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>Monty? I'll text you
the address.</i>

23
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:53,233
<i>Go there, I'll take care of you.</i>

24
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:55,433
<i> Glen, what are you doing?</i>

25
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:57,200
<i> Boss, sorry, Monty escaped.</i>

26
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,867
<i>I know! There are a lot of them,
but they're all stupid!</i>

27
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,267
<i> You're ruined my schedule.</i>

28
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,667
<i> Wait for me to get there.</i>

29
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,433
<i> I'll kill that idiot myself.</i>

30
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:06,800
<i> I hope my suspicion is wrong.</i>

31
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:14,533
Ma'am Sophia...

32
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:19,367
I'm sorry about those two.

33
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,267
Don't worry.
I'll reprimand them.

34
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,033
Bobby, you should know better

35
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:29,767
than to bring your gutter
friends to this event.

36
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:31,867
Our reputation will be ruined.

37
00:01:33,767 --> 00:01:34,900
Sorry again.

38
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:38,400
Okay, I'll just go find father.

39
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:43,400
Oh, and now you call
my husband father?

40
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:46,900
You're really fuzzy!

41
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:50,133
You pretend you can't
call him father,

42
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:53,200
but you're planning to do it
on his birthday.

43
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:55,233
You're really a smart-aleck,
aren't you?

44
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,833
I don't have
any plans like that.

45
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:02,667
But you won't believe me,

46
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:06,367
so I won't waste my time
explaining.

47
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:11,233
Ma'am Sophia, I just want
to give you some advice.

48
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:13,867
Don't get too angry

49
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,767
because it's obvious that
you're 70 something years old.

50
00:02:19,933 --> 00:02:20,700
Okay.

51
00:02:25,667 --> 00:02:26,933
Madam...

52
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:28,800
Are you 70 something?

53
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:31,100
- Stupid!
- Oh...

54
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,900
I'm just asking.

55
00:02:43,933 --> 00:02:45,533
Dizon, behind you!

56
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:53,733
Bok, how are you?

57
00:02:53,867 --> 00:02:55,433
I'm okay.

58
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,833
They took Monty.

59
00:03:01,967 --> 00:03:03,533
We need to get him back.

60
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:04,967
There are too many of them.

61
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,200
Sir!

62
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,467
Move!

63
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,600
Move!

64
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,333
No more?

65
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,133
What?

66
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:09,600
You're nothing!

67
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:10,467
What?

68
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,200
What?

69
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:20,300
- Sir, are you okay?
- Sir...

70
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,767
Sir, Lieutenant Dizon needs
to be taken to the hospital.

71
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,600
Bautista, you take him.

72
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,367
We still need to find Monty.

73
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,600
Sir, we'll take care of this.

74
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,533
Take Sir Fred to the hospital.

75
00:04:38,967 --> 00:04:41,367
- Wow, that looks delicious.
- Bobby...

76
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:42,533
Faye!

77
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:45,033
- How are you? Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

78
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:48,800
It's fun, and the food
looks delicious.

79
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:50,600
Oh, Bobby, sorry, huh?

80
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:52,600
I heard what happened
with your friends.

81
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,733
Mar and Abdul...

82
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:56,900
No, that's my fault too.

83
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:59,267
I shouldn't have invited them.

84
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,167
No, Bobby,
you did nothing wrong.

85
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:04,433
And for sure,
daddy also wants...

86
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:07,133
to see your friends
who live with you.

87
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,333
Has daddy told you yet?

88
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,567
Which one?

89
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,333
He's planning to announce
at the party

90
00:05:15,467 --> 00:05:16,867
that you're his daughter.

91
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,867
Isn't that exciting?

92
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,667
What?

93
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,133
Yes.

94
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:25,733
I'm so happy, Bobby.

95
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:39,500
Oh, okay, Bobby just eat a lot.

96
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:41,033
- The food here is delicious.
- Okay...

97
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:42,400
- thank you.
- Okay.

98
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:04,167
"My situation here is
difficult."

99
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:07,033
Monty is definitely
not there, Chief.

100
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,067
We've already covered
the area

101
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,967
where Lieutenant Garcia
was ambushed.

102
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,100
Thank you very much, Bautista.

103
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,833
Do another sweep of the area.

104
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:18,267
Then, come back here
to the station.

105
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,400
Copy, Chief.

106
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:34,967
Cerbito.

107
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,000
You need to help us.

108
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:48,067
Did Monty mention to you
where he could go and hide?

109
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,367
Nothing, Sir.

110
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:53,733
I didn't know
he was going to escape.

111
00:06:54,433 --> 00:06:55,633
Just make sure.

112
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,667
If we don't find Monty,

113
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,467
this will badly affect
your case.

114
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:03,767
No, Sir.

115
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:08,600
Didn't I tell you that I'm not
involved in his work?

116
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:16,333
I still can't believe he'd just
leave me locked up here.

117
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:27,200
Hello, Tonyo?

118
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,100
Oh, what's that you texted

119
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,467
that your situation
is difficult there?

120
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,200
<i> - Are you okay?
-</i> Sorry.

121
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,500
I shouldn't have texted you.

122
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:36,533
I'm sorry.

123
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,200
What's with you?

124
00:07:39,967 --> 00:07:42,433
Of course, I want you
to talk to me right away,

125
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:44,267
whenever something
happens in your life.

126
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,100
What happened?

127
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,700
You know that Ma'am Sophia
doesn't like me, right?

128
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,067
Then I heard
from Faye earlier

129
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,700
that father is going
to announce

130
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,067
that I am her daughter
here at the party.

131
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,233
What should I do?

132
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:02,400
Why? Don't you want
to be introduced?

133
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:05,100
I don't know.

134
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,733
Well, if I were
in your situation,

135
00:08:08,533 --> 00:08:10,733
I probably wouldn't know
what I would do either.

136
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,367
Have you talked to your father?

137
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:16,800
Not yet.

138
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:18,667
It might be better...

139
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,300
if you talk to him first

140
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,667
so he knows how you're feeling.

141
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:28,100
Who knows,
he'll change his mind?

142
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:33,267
Or he can change your mind.

143
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:37,300
Yeah, right.

144
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:39,433
I'll just talk to him.

145
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:40,900
Thanks, Tonyo.

146
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:42,600
Sorry again.

147
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:45,667
You're really annoying,
aren't you?

148
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,833
One more sorry,

149
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,767
and I'll spread the word
that we're a couple.

150
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:49,867
What?

151
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,467
No, just kidding.

152
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:56,367
Just text or call if you need
someone to talk to, okay?

153
00:08:56,533 --> 00:08:57,933
Okay, thanks again.

154
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:05,133
What are you doing here, Glen?

155
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:25,500
- Miss...
- Yes, Ma'am?

156
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:29,100
Aren't you the housekeeper
of the Mayor's family?

157
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:31,033
Oh, yes, Ma'am.
Why, Ma'am?

158
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,700
Do you happen to know
where he is?

159
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:36,667
Oh, I don't know, Ma'am.

160
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:39,300
Maybe his bodyguards would know,

161
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:41,133
since they're always with him,
Ma'am.

162
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,267
All right, thank you.

163
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:58,400
- Mister...
- Ma'am?

164
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,567
Do you know where the mayor is?

165
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:01,800
I don't, Ma'am.

166
00:11:03,267 --> 00:11:04,567
- How about you, Mister?
- Ma'am?

167
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:07,667
The mayor, do you know
where he is?

168
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,033
I don't either, Ma'am.

169
00:11:21,533 --> 00:11:22,767
Sir Tonyo...

170
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:23,900
Selena.

171
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:25,967
I brought you some fruit.

172
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:29,533
Thank you so much.

173
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:34,933
But you know, you don't have
to do these things.

174
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:38,033
Do what?
Bring you fruit?

175
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,100
It's nothing.

176
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:43,233
You're being overly dramatic.

177
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:49,033
But still, thank you,
because despite everything...

178
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:53,000
you still helped me fix
that date with Bobby.

179
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:56,700
Am I a masochist?

180
00:11:56,833 --> 00:12:01,267
Well, isn't that how it is
when you love someone?

181
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,400
But don't worry, Sir Tonyo.

182
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:07,067
I also know
how to accept defeat.

183
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:10,900
You're not a loser, Selena.

184
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:16,733
But I hope that one day,

185
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:20,533
you'll also find the perfect
person for you.

186
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:23,567
I hope so.

187
00:12:24,233 --> 00:12:27,300
It would be such
a waste of my beauty.

188
00:12:27,433 --> 00:12:30,933
Anyway, I'll just follow up
with your nurse, okay?

189
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:31,867
Okay.

190
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,367
Boss, thank you so much
for helping me escape.

191
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:44,700
Think nothing of it.

192
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:46,367
You know you're one of my men.

193
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:48,500
Thank you, Boss.
Really.

194
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:51,800
Boss, what's our plan?

195
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:53,967
Anything, you can order me
to do anything.

196
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:00,900
Relax.

197
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:02,900
You need to take it easy.

198
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:04,600
There are just some things
I want to know.

199
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:08,967
Like, your girlfriend Jhem...

200
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:12,267
does she know anything about me?

201
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,467
Sir, Sir, no, Sir,
cross my heart.

202
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,767
I even pity her.

203
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,467
Oh, so you pity her.

204
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,400
Don't worry.

205
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:24,367
Even if we can't get her
to escape,

206
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:27,067
we can still clear her name.

207
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:41,367
- Kneel!
- Boss, what is this?

208
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,000
Boss, what do you mean by this?

209
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,533
What is this, Boss?

210
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:45,967
What are you going to do?

211
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:50,767
Boss...

212
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,300
- Bok.
- Bok...

213
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:57,767
What are you doing here?

214
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,433
We ran into trouble
while transferring Monty.

215
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:01,567
What happened?

216
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:04,333
They blocked us
and he got taken away.

217
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,900
Dizon was shot too,
he's here at the hospital.

218
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,400
How's Dizon?

219
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,767
He's okay, the wound
isn't that bad.

220
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,033
That's good to hear.

221
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:17,333
So what's the latest on Monty?

222
00:14:17,467 --> 00:14:19,433
Still nothing, Bok.
There's still no news.

223
00:14:20,033 --> 00:14:22,733
Last we heard,
he still hasn't been seen.

224
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:24,567
You know, Bok,

225
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,800
whoever's got Monty
really means business.

226
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:30,033
It's getting annoying.

227
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:33,067
Our cases just keep piling up
but none get solved.

228
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,167
It's fine, Bok.

229
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:37,467
As soon as I can,
I'll help right away.

230
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:41,000
I'm just going to get a coffee.

231
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,067
Want anything?

232
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:43,767
I'm okay, thanks.

233
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:45,867
All right, I'll be back.

234
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:50,333
I'll pester you guys to death!

235
00:14:50,467 --> 00:14:51,700
I was even invited here!

236
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:53,300
- Sir, you really can't!
- Faye Guerrero, dude!

237
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:54,567
- You're such a pest!
- Faye Guerrero!

238
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:56,433
- You really can't! Get out!
- That's mayor's daughter.

239
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:58,400
- Mister, what's that?
-Here she comes, here she comes.

240
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:00,567
He's my guest.
Let go of him.

241
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,900
Sorry, Ma'am.

242
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:05,367
- I told you so.
- It's okay.

243
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:06,867
You guys are hard-headed.

244
00:15:08,733 --> 00:15:10,167
Sorry about that, Vince.

245
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:14,633
No, it's fine.
I'm used to people like that.

246
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:19,933
I'm actually happy to see you.

247
00:15:20,167 --> 00:15:21,333
Good thing you came.

248
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:23,267
Allan said you were busy.

249
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,267
What? Allan?

250
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:28,900
Hey.

251
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:30,800
Vince.

252
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:32,833
You're here too.

253
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:36,567
Actually, I've been here
for a while.

254
00:15:36,733 --> 00:15:38,567
Faye and I already talked
about a lot of things.

255
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,867
Hey, that stays between us,
okay.

256
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,867
Don't worry.

257
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:44,133
I'm great at keeping secrets.

258
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,167
Oh, guys, I'll leave you
for a bit, okay.

259
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:49,667
I'm just going
to look for my dad.

260
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,667
Oh, go ahead.

261
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,233
The program's about to start.

262
00:15:52,367 --> 00:15:53,433
- Go ahead, go ahead.
- Go, Faye.

263
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:55,300
- All right.
- I'll take care of Vince.

264
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:56,367
See you later.

265
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:00,033
Do you have a problem, Bro?

266
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,633
What? Wait,
what problem, Vince?

267
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:06,000
Are you trying to impress Faye?

268
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:08,267
Vince.

269
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,633
Do you think I'd start showing
off in this situation?

270
00:16:10,767 --> 00:16:14,167
I'm just taking it slow, Vince.

271
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:15,900
And I'm not impulsive.

272
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:17,800
Taking it slow?
What do you mean, slow?

273
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:20,300
Bro, okay, let me
explain to you.

274
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:23,233
Since you don't seem
to get the situation.

275
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:24,667
Go.

276
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:27,200
I met Faye first.

277
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,567
You don't even know
what I went through

278
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,600
to get close to her,

279
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,233
and then you butting in
like it's nothing?

280
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,100
Bro, do you understand
what I'm saying?

281
00:16:35,667 --> 00:16:39,067
Don't ruin my strategy.

282
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:40,900
Hold on, Bro.

283
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:43,067
Mind if I ask you something?

284
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:44,233
What is it?

285
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,867
Is Faye your girlfriend?

286
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:51,967
Not yet, right?

287
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:56,000
So, as far as I'm concerned,
all's fair.

288
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:58,300
I'm not doing anything wrong,

289
00:16:58,433 --> 00:16:59,600
not stepping on anyone.

290
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:00,800
Bro...

291
00:17:02,467 --> 00:17:03,933
may the best man win.

292
00:17:05,067 --> 00:17:05,700
Okay?

293
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:09,433
Looks like I finished my drink.

294
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,667
I'll just get a refill, okay?

295
00:17:12,867 --> 00:17:14,400
May the best man win...

296
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,767
What a meddler.

297
00:17:27,067 --> 00:17:28,000
Oh...

298
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:30,900
Ma'am Bobby, I'll go ahead now.

299
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:32,533
Thanks again for the food, okay?

300
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:34,300
All right, Noble.
Take care, okay?

301
00:17:34,433 --> 00:17:37,400
And call me again if there's any
news about Jun Alferez.

302
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,433
Okay, Ma'am.

303
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:44,567
Bobby!

304
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:46,533
Did you see daddy?

305
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,133
Not yet.

306
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:49,933
Of all the times to show up,

307
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:52,233
daddy shows up when they need
him for the program...

308
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:57,733
Bobby, if you see daddy, tell
him to go to the stage, okay?

309
00:17:57,967 --> 00:17:58,667
Sure.

310
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,333
- Thanks, Bobby.
- Sure, okay.

311
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:01,400
Thank you.

312
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:15,300
Boss, what are you doing?

313
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:16,600
Have mercy on me, please.

314
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:19,600
Boss, I'm one of your
most loyal people.

315
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:28,400
What happened to him?

316
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:32,033
Why isn't he answering?

317
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,167
Boss, if it weren't for me,

318
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:37,067
your pimple-patch drugs
wouldn't have grown.

319
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,767
Yes, I messed up,

320
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:42,200
but believe me, Boss.

321
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:45,567
Whatever your next business is,
pick me.

322
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,200
You know, if you could talk...

323
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:53,700
Do you think you're the one
who made my business grow?

324
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,033
Remember this, Monty.

325
00:18:57,733 --> 00:18:58,967
You're just one of my men.

326
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:00,500
I know that.

327
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:01,833
Please, have mercy.

328
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,800
Don't do this.

329
00:19:04,667 --> 00:19:06,267
I didn't wrong you, okay.

330
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,533
Do you know
what I hate most, Monty?

331
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,700
Do you know?

332
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:17,500
That the one who's threatening
me will talk...

333
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,333
because he didn't get
what he wanted.

334
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:21,967
Boss, I wouldn't really do that.

335
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,400
What?

336
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:24,800
I only said that because,
Boss...

337
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,233
What?

338
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,033
Boss, we'll take care of this.

339
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,333
Really, Dante?

340
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:48,200
You'll take care of it?

341
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,300
Are you sure?

342
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:52,967
But didn't the last time
I buried him for you,

343
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,467
the dogs just dug him up?

344
00:19:55,367 --> 00:19:56,267
Right?

345
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,200
Boss, should we dig
the grave deeper?

346
00:19:58,333 --> 00:19:59,933
Oh, deeper...

347
00:20:00,067 --> 00:20:02,400
So smart of you, you only just
thought of that now?

348
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:04,333
You only thought
of that now?

349
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:05,233
Idiot!

350
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:09,533
Chop him up and dump him in
different parts of the river!

351
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,667
You're not thinking.

352
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,033
Boss...

353
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:30,700
Is there a problem?

354
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:32,367
Nothing.

355
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:33,900
Just fix that.

356
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,567
Fix it.
That's on you.

357
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:49,667
Hello, Dad?

358
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:51,033
Bobby...

359
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:54,967
I'm at the end
of Hidalgo Street.

360
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:59,633
I'm beside the abandoned
warehouse.

361
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:16,233
Where's my husband?

362
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,167
Oh, I don't know, Ma'am.

363
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:19,333
I'm here...

364
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:21,967
I think Bobby knows where he is.

365
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,867
Bobby has been looking for daddy
for some time now.

366
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,033
Mama Zondra!

367
00:22:27,167 --> 00:22:30,367
I don't know what it feels like
to lose someone you love.

368
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:32,633
But when you're put
in that situation,

369
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:34,467
you really don't know
what to do.

370
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:36,033
Alma, help me.

371
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:38,133
The killer has to be caught.

372
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:41,600
Alma.

373
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:43,300
What are you doing here?

374
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:46,967
I'm here to ask if you know
Mama Zondra.

375
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:47,933
By the way, how's Bobby?

376
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,033
You're such an amazing cop,

377
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:51,400
yet as a lover,
you're a pathetic creature.

378
00:22:51,533 --> 00:22:52,500
It's true.

379
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:53,800
What do you mean by that?
